Test of Statistical Theory of Nuclear Reactions
at 24 keV.
Antimony-Beryllium, 1.7cm diam. * 3.3cm height,
flux approximately 10**7 neutrons/sec
Powder, purity better than 99.9%, sample sandwiched
between 2 cellotapes, perspex ring for fixed geometry
activation. Beta activity measured
end window beta counter
I-127(n,gamma)I-128 sigma = 0.82 barn
assumed
